# Walkthrough - Plugin Model Addition & Verification

I have successfully updated the plugin feature to allow dynamic model addition with automated verification. The entire flow has been tested and verified end-to-end.

## Changes Made

### Universal Test Script
- Created [test_model_integration.py](file:///Users/mk/Documents/chatbot-ai-systems-production/scripts/test_model_integration.py) to verify model connectivity and tool calling capabilities.
- Fixed a bug in tool formatting ([to_ollama_format](file:///Users/mk/Documents/chatbot-ai-systems-production/src/chatbot_ai_system/tools/base.py#14-24)) that was causing verification failures for models with tools.

### Backend Infrastructure
- Updated [schemas.py](file:///Users/mk/Documents/chatbot-ai-systems-production/src/chatbot_ai_system/models/schemas.py) and [settings_manager.py](file:///Users/mk/Documents/chatbot-ai-systems-production/src/chatbot_ai_system/config/settings_manager.py) to support dynamic configuration of LLM providers.
- Implemented `/api/plugins/add-model` in [routes.py](file:///Users/mk/Documents/chatbot-ai-systems-production/src/chatbot_ai_system/server/routes.py).

### Frontend Dashboard
- Redesigned [PluginsDashboard.tsx](file:///Users/mk/Documents/chatbot-ai-systems-production/frontend/components/PluginsDashboard.tsx):
    - **Refined Alignment**: Moved "Add New Model" to the Active Model area for better visibility.
    - **Multi-step Modal**: Type selection -> Configuration -> Real-time Verification.

